Privacy Policy
Last Modified: November 4, 2022
Thank you for using our products and services! We respect your concerns about privacy and thank you for your trust in us.
If you have any questions about any content in this privacy policy or exercise any rights you might own, you may find our contact information in the "Contact Us" section.
Please note that you can contact our data protection officer to request the deletion of your data through the contact information provided by us.
Before using our products or services, please read and thoroughly understand this policy, especially the terms that are in bold and/or underlined, which you should read them carefully. You should use the relevant products or products after fully understanding and agreeing to them. Once you start to use our products or services, it means that you have fully understood and agreed to this policy.
This privacy policy will help you understand:
1.
We will collect and obtain your personal information via the following ways
1.1 Information you voluntarily provide
Information you voluntarily provide to us when you accept or use services we provide, including
When you register an account, you can use an account from a third party, such as Facebook, QQ, WeChat, Line, and Apple to log in to our product. In doing so, you are required to provide us with your third-party account's avatar, username, account ID, and other information.
You can also choose to directly enter our product as a guest.
When you use our related services, such as Feedback, we might ask you to provide certain personal information, including
your account, E-mail address, phone number, device ID, system language, APP version, and other relevant information you voluntarily provide to us.
1.2 Information we collect from you
we need to collect device information from you,
including
device name, device model, Advertisement Identifiers (include
IDFA
, IDFV), operating system, application version and type related to the operations users execute on devices and behaviors of users, language settings, resolution, and mobile endpoint random storage,
in order to guarantee the safe running of software and services.
In order to provide you with the basic functions of our products and/or services, we may need to collect the following personal information from you by invoking device permissions:
(a) Native or H5 events vary in channels and regions. The
location permission
of the device you are using is required in order to achieve diversity and accuracy.
(b) When you are using related features to voluntarily provide images or save images, we need
write and read permissions to your Album
to ensure that the game functions normally for you.
(c) When you are willing to receive related game information, including notifications regarding updates, maintenance, and changes, we will request
application notification permission
to be able to notify you.
(d) When you are using related features and need to take photos, we will
request
permission to use your camera
in order to ensure the feature works uninterruptedly.
(e) In order to improve your gameplay, we might request
App Tracking permission
(Please update your system version to the latest.).
Tips for specific function permissions: If you need to turn off the function permissions that are turned on to use the above-mentioned specific functions, most mobile devices will support your needs. For detailed methods, please refer to or contact the service provider or manufacturer of your mobile device. You can also contact us for assistance.
Please note that individual device information, application notification permission, application tracking permissions, and others cannot identify specific natural persons' information. If we combine this non-personal information with other information to identify the identities of specific natural persons or combine other personal information together, this type of non-personal information will be regarded as personal information which shall be anonymized and de-identified during the combination period unless you are authorized or the laws and regulations demand otherwise.
2.Third Party Operators
In-App Purchase: You can acquire virtual products (used for this game only) related to our products and their related services,
including game items, auto-sub, and in-game Ads-Free via purchasing, depending on
the product
. The above said payment service is provided by Apple. We will only receive
verification results
confirming that you have completed the payment process from the Apple payment service provider, then provide corresponding products and services to you.
If you wish to learn the specific rules as to how Apple service provider collects personal information, please read Apple's privacy policy.
The following is a complete list of the third-party operators we currently use in our services. They have their own privacy policies.
In order to maximize the security of your information, we strongly recommend that you check their privacy policies before using the services provided by third-party service providers.
Third Party SDK
